    <node id="Smoking History">
      <data key="d0">Smoking History</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Smoking History is a data variable utilized across multiple datasets and tables, such as Satpathy.csv, Table Cao from source9, the Gillette table from source12, and the Wang table of Source18, as well as in the Huang dataset. This variable systematically documents patients' smoking backgrounds by capturing a range of information about smoking behavior.

The Smoking History field encompasses details about an individual's past and present smoking habits, including whether the person is a lifelong non-smoker, a current smoker, or a reformed smoker, and in certain datasets, whether reformation occurred within the past 15 years. It specifies both daily and non-daily smoking patterns, as well as records on exposure to smoking. Additionally, Smoking History documents lifetime cigarette consumption and categorizes the patient's status accordingly, allowing for the identification of nuanced smoking histories such as current reformed smokers or those with significant exposure but not active habits.

By including these comprehensive attributes, the Smoking History variable enables a detailed understanding of each patient's smoking timeline and categorizes individuals based on current, former, or never-smoker status. Such documentation is essential for analyses that rely on accurate representations of smoking behavior across diverse patient populations and research datasets.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-eb6086be52202affaf1f5509e67c615c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9757b1506341f57b070dd345cbe2369b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6540e1b69b541bfe99426e59fb9627a4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5672e0298c4f15068d4fae15f25e782&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-efe96eed9593ab805239b1a121351ac4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f35709cd063c7f945768e5ca53cbe7fe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0c3c12a65d99f3fd6fb254162ad5f01&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56d9b31e2fe71c27aaee333b1280d702</data>
