    <node id="Age">
      <data key="d0">Age</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Age is a data field widely recorded across multiple biomedical datasets, consumer profiles, and research tables. It consistently refers to the chronological age of individuals, patients, or participants, typically documented as part of demographic information for each sample or case.

In clinical and cancer research contexts, Age is a column or field included in datasets such as Vasaikar.csv, Huang.csv Table, Cao table, Dou data table, Clark table from source10, Gillette table from source12, Satpathy dataset, and Wang table from Source18. It specifically represents the patient's or participant's age in years, accompanying each cancer or disease sample to provide vital demographic context. The field records numeric values denoting the number of years lived by each individual, with sample values cited ranging from '20.0', '3.0', and '77.0' to '42', '68', '69', '72', '30', and '63'. Age is typically formatted as an integer or float, depending on the dataset.

In Consumer Profiles, Age similarly functions as a field representing the age of consumers. It uses numeric values, further demonstrating the versatility and importance of this demographic attribute across diverse research and application domains.

Overall, Age serves as a fundamental variable for characterizing individuals in biomedical studies, consumer profiling, and other datasets, providing a standardized measure of chronological age in years for each sample or participant. This allows researchers, analysts, and data curators to assess demographic distributions, explore associations with clinical or behavioral outcomes, and integrate age as an essential component in data-driven analyses.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9d9939ff094898f5ac26a9ca6b9f24d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9757b1506341f57b070dd345cbe2369b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-940356a2b7fb1da402acf0a10ad5efd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6783528b0da3a76298806176cbbbcd4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07e1af1bf39bca6afef0e83065e9d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6540e1b69b541bfe99426e59fb9627a4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ad678bf5a7ea6b0d9c70dfb59122643&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0042ea9e8cc625b46ea0b34af2adba03&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c8a40c856b719c354d215bc913c1e47&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ee593816b40e1f778329f1904c2877d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-efe96eed9593ab805239b1a121351ac4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-44fbd23d798d1dc0e4bb45cbbb15a452&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0c3c12a65d99f3fd6fb254162ad5f01&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4cdc7d5a512e452fb24328ea78eddeff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56d9b31e2fe71c27aaee333b1280d702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42f6c221f8c2991eeb0a288c0638a1e4</data>
