    <node id="Source11">
      <data key="d0">Source11</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Source11 is a primary data source and origin of detailed proteogenomic and clinical metadata, as utilized in the study "Proteogenomic Characterization of Endometrial Carcinoma" by Dou et al. This entity provides comprehensive information on patient demographics, tumor characteristics, molecular profiles, clinical and pathology data, and supports the Dou data table utilized within the research context.

As the foundational source for the Dou table, Source11 supplies the data lineage for all the fields listed therein, encompassing immunological cell population measurements, sample data, and genomic information. The dataset attributed to Source11 underlies several key data fields in Table Dou, including those referencing RNA sequencing, methylation, gene interactions, pathway activations, and genetic variation indicators.

In summary, Source11 is consistently cited as the originating dataset for the Dou table, serving as the referenced authority for both core sample and extended molecular data fields across the described research materials. Its role ensures that all referenced data uphold provenance, traceability, and comprehensive metadata coverage relevant to proteogenomic, clinical, and genetic study dimensions.</data>
