      <data key="d0">Tumor Site</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Tumor Site records the anatomical location of the tumor within the pancreas, such as head and tail.&lt;SEP&gt;Tumor Site specifies the location of the tumor within the organ, such as 'Lower pole', 'Upper pole', or 'Anterior endometrium'.&lt;SEP&gt;Tumor Site describes the anatomical location of tumors in samples, including 'Anterior endometrium', 'Posterior endometrium', and 'Other, specify'.&lt;SEP&gt;Tumor Site indicates the anatomic location of the tumor, both in original and curated terms.&lt;SEP&gt;Tumor Site is a field in the Cao table denoting anatomical location, with sample values such as head and tail.&lt;SEP&gt;Tumor Site describes the location of a tumor within the endometrium of the uterus.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9757b1506341f57b070dd345cbe2369b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2e9a61ac0d1c7927b0d4e0b05cde5a6a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07e1af1bf39bca6afef0e83065e9d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ad678bf5a7ea6b0d9c70dfb59122643&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d65ba32b88e919e45abe4e167e142224&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4cdc7d5a512e452fb24328ea78eddeff</data>
