      <data key="d0">Histologic Type</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Histologic Type records the histologic classification of specimens in the Clark Table.&lt;SEP&gt;Histologic Type refers to the classification of tumor cells, such as 'Clear cell renal cell carcinoma' or 'Endometrioid'.&lt;SEP&gt;Histologic Type classifies the tumor based on microscopic cellular features, such as squamous cell carcinoma.&lt;SEP&gt;Histologic Type identifies the histologic subtype of the tumor, reported as endometrioid for all samples.&lt;SEP&gt;Histologic Type refers to the specific type of histologic diagnosis, specifically squamous cell carcinoma.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9757b1506341f57b070dd345cbe2369b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07e1af1bf39bca6afef0e83065e9d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ad678bf5a7ea6b0d9c70dfb59122643&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5672e0298c4f15068d4fae15f25e782&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cab940e1fe00d1b5b4f017b4600051e5</data>
