    <node id="Ethnicity">
      <data key="d0">Ethnicity</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Ethnicity is a demographic attribute commonly recorded in biological and clinical data tables to indicate the ethnic background of participants, patients, or sample donors. Across multiple datasets such as the Clark Table, Dou Table, Gillette Table from source12, Krug Table, McDermott Table, Satpathy Table, and Wang Table of Source18, Ethnicity serves to categorize individuals according to their reported ethnic background.

Typically, Ethnicity is recorded using descriptors such as 'Hispanic or Latino' and 'Not-Hispanic or Latino', reflecting whether the individual identifies as Hispanic. In certain datasets, the field is further specified; for example, the Dou Table records individuals primarily as Not-Hispanic or Latino, while the Gillette Table emphasizes participants of primarily caucasian background. The Krug Table and related datasets categorize samples using descriptors such as 'black.or.african.american' and 'white', focusing on classifications like black or African American and white.

In summary, Ethnicity represents the reported ethnic background for each participant, sample donor, or patient and is used for demographic categorization. While the specifics and terminology may vary slightly between datasets, Ethnicity remains a standardized field for capturing and recording an individual's ethnic identity in clinical and research settings.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2e9a61ac0d1c7927b0d4e0b05cde5a6a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6783528b0da3a76298806176cbbbcd4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07e1af1bf39bca6afef0e83065e9d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-53356444f3701ca3b0e9c4e5fc538534&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-39acc73375d88275246fd82938b8a9d9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ee593816b40e1f778329f1904c2877d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-efe96eed9593ab805239b1a121351ac4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b761bae97b278ce0ffbfd47de082593a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8eb0d488bbf0573d3ad35307e37d1534&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56d9b31e2fe71c27aaee333b1280d702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42f6c221f8c2991eeb0a288c0638a1e4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1772772466</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
