    <node id="Tumor Focality">
      <data key="d0">Tumor Focality</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Tumor Focality describes whether the tumor is unifocal or multifocal.&lt;SEP&gt;Tumor Focality records whether the tumor is unifocal in the provided samples.&lt;SEP&gt;Tumor Focality indicates whether the tumor consists of a single (unifocal) or multiple (multifocal) lesions within the affected tissue or organ.&lt;SEP&gt;Tumor Focality is a field in the Cao table describing tumor characteristics, with sample value Unifocal.&lt;SEP&gt;Tumor Focality indicates whether a tumor has a single site (unifocal) or multiple sites (multifocal).&lt;SEP&gt;Tumor Focality specifies whether the tumor is unifocal or multifocal.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2e9a61ac0d1c7927b0d4e0b05cde5a6a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07e1af1bf39bca6afef0e83065e9d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ad678bf5a7ea6b0d9c70dfb59122643&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5672e0298c4f15068d4fae15f25e782&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d65ba32b88e919e45abe4e167e142224&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4cdc7d5a512e452fb24328ea78eddeff</data>
