      <data key="d2">Tumor Size Cm records the size of the tumor in centimeters.&lt;SEP&gt;Tumor Size Cm represents the measured size of tumors in centimeters for each sample.&lt;SEP&gt;Tumor Size Cm is a field in the Cao table measuring tumor size in centimeters, with sample values such as 3.0, 2.7, and 5.0.&lt;SEP&gt;Tumor Size Cm records the size of the tumor measured in centimeters.</data>
