    <node id="Perineural Invasion">
      <data key="d0">Perineural Invasion</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Perineural Invasion details whether tumor cells have invaded nerves.&lt;SEP&gt;Perineural Invasion denotes tumor spread along or around nerves.&lt;SEP&gt;Perineural Invasion is a pathological feature captured in Table Cao, indicating if tumor cells are present in or around nerves.&lt;SEP&gt;Perineural Invasion reports if there is tumor invasion into perineural spaces, as documented in the Vasaikar table.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-61e42152f676545c1a94912cb5944a32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07e1af1bf39bca6afef0e83065e9d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a16fce68df8a087312002be8f90c5ca4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b74bb3e12c83406f44983363ccf9e2f</data>
