    <node id="Vital Status">
      <data key="d0">Vital Status</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Vital Status records survival status of participants, with deceased as the outcome.&lt;SEP&gt;Vital Status records if the patient was living or deceased at follow-up.&lt;SEP&gt;Vital Status indicates whether the individuals associated with the samples are deceased.&lt;SEP&gt;Vital Status records whether the patient is deceased or alive, and in this sample, all patients are marked as deceased, based on Table Cao from source9.&lt;SEP&gt;Vital Status indicates whether the patient is currently living or deceased, as recorded in the Vasaikar table.&lt;SEP&gt;Vital Status indicates the status of the patient at last contact, such as deceased.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-61e42152f676545c1a94912cb5944a32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ab74d66b8e2d613e98ac4eee37a5670c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07e1af1bf39bca6afef0e83065e9d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a16fce68df8a087312002be8f90c5ca4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b4ffc9e2845d3b0bbdc6573abf49b187&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f35709cd063c7f945768e5ca53cbe7fe</data>
