      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Sex">
      <data key="d0">Sex</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Sex records the biological sex of participants.&lt;SEP&gt;Sex is a field in the Cao table recording participant sex, with sample values like Male and Female.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-07e1af1bf39bca6afef0e83065e9d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4cdc7d5a512e452fb24328ea78eddeff</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1772772539</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Race">
      <data key="d0">Race</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Race records the racial background of participants in the study.&lt;SEP&gt;Race indicates the racial identification of patients, such as 'White'.&lt;SEP&gt;Race is a field in the Cao table recording participant race, with sample values like White.&lt;SEP&gt;Race indicates the racial background of patients, as recorded in the data table Dou.&lt;SEP&gt;Race is a field in the Clark table in source10, recording the race of individuals, with sample values 'White'.&lt;SEP&gt;Race documents the patient's race for each case in the McDermott table.&lt;SEP&gt;Race records the race of the individual as specified in the Wang table of Source18.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-07e1af1bf39bca6afef0e83065e9d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ad678bf5a7ea6b0d9c70dfb59122643&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ee593816b40e1f778329f1904c2877d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-efe96eed9593ab805239b1a121351ac4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-44fbd23d798d1dc0e4bb45cbbb15a452&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8eb0d488bbf0573d3ad35307e37d1534&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4cdc7d5a512e452fb24328ea78eddeff</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
