    </node>
    <node id="Tumor Necrosis">
      <data key="d0">Tumor Necrosis</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Tumor Necrosis describes the presence or absence of necrosis in tumor samples.&lt;SEP&gt;Tumor Necrosis is a pathological field recorded in Table Cao, indicating whether necrosis is identified in a tumor sample.&lt;SEP&gt;Tumor Necrosis is a field in the Cao table, with sample values like Not identified representing the presence or absence of tissue death within tumors.&lt;SEP&gt;Tumor necrosis refers to the presence or absence of dead tissue within a tumor, as assessed in the sample.&lt;SEP&gt;Tumor Necrosis indicates the presence or absence of necrosis within the tumor tissue.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-07e1af1bf39bca6afef0e83065e9d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5672e0298c4f15068d4fae15f25e782&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b6c4353453062918d9e8207fa5ac801&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4cdc7d5a512e452fb24328ea78eddeff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b74bb3e12c83406f44983363ccf9e2f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1772772486</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Lymph Vascular Invasion">
      <data key="d0">Lymph Vascular Invasion</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Lymph Vascular Invasion indicates the presence of lymphatic or vascular invasion by tumor cells.&lt;SEP&gt;Lymph Vascular Invasion is a pathological characteristic recorded in Table Cao, describing the presence or absence of tumor invasion into lymphatic or vascular structures.&lt;SEP&gt;Lymph Vascular Invasion is a field in the Cao table describing whether lymph or vascular invasion was identified.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-07e1af1bf39bca6afef0e83065e9d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4cdc7d5a512e452fb24328ea78eddeff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b74bb3e12c83406f44983363ccf9e2f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
