    <node id="Missense_Mutation">
      <data key="d0">Missense_Mutation</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Missense_Mutation refers to a type of point mutation where a single nucleotide change results in a codon that codes for a different amino acid.&lt;SEP&gt;Missense_Mutation is a type of genetic mutation, commonly seen in fields such as NF1.mutation, PIK3CA.mutation, and NOTCH1.mutation in the Satpathy data set.&lt;SEP&gt;Missense_Mutation is a type of genetic alteration which results in a single amino acid substitution in a protein.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ef50a779ee9b01547f7b4ecb81de4aa3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0a609c332695ee10881d19b03221d781&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81847cb9abb5eeae6f99e3ef595ac88b</data>
