    <node id="Frame_Shift_Del">
      <data key="d0">Frame_Shift_Del</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Frame_Shift_Del represents a frameshift deletion mutation, causing a shift in the reading frame of the gene.&lt;SEP&gt;Frame_Shift_Del is a type of genetic mutation found as a sample in NF1.mutation in the Satpathy data set.&lt;SEP&gt;Frame_Shift_Del is a type of genetic alteration involving the deletion of nucleotides that shifts the reading frame, often resulting in altered protein function.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ef50a779ee9b01547f7b4ecb81de4aa3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0a609c332695ee10881d19b03221d781&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81847cb9abb5eeae6f99e3ef595ac88b</data>
