      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Type is a field in Consumer Profiles indicating the kind or classification of a profile, with sample values such as 'PEL0', 'LED1', and 'lat2'.&lt;SEP&gt;Type refers to the classification of the sample, such as tumor or normal adjacent tissue, in the Gillette table from source12.&lt;SEP&gt;Type indicates whether the sample is natural (NAT) or a tumor as recorded in the Satpathy table.</data>
