    <node id="Experiment">
      <data key="d0">Experiment</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Experiment is an identifier for the specific experiment or study associated with Table Gillette, indicated by numeric values.&lt;SEP&gt;Experiment is an identifier for the specific experiment or study conducted, represented as an int64 field in the Gillette table from source12.&lt;SEP&gt;Experiment is an identifier for the specific experiment or batch related to the sample data.&lt;SEP&gt;Experiment refers to the specific experiment or batch for which the identifier field is provided.</data>
